# Per-listing landing pages live on the ctvreel-agent app at
# realestate.ctvhomes.com/l/{slug}. Burning that long subdomain into a CTV ad
# would be a mouthful — agents say "ctvhomes.com slash 419 Quaker" much more
# naturally.
#
# IMPORTANT: the order of these rules matters. Netlify processes them top to
# bottom, first match wins. Static-asset paths (_next, api) need to proxy
# straight through WITHOUT the /l/ prefix — otherwise the browser's request
# for /_next/static/chunks/foo.css gets rewritten to /l/_next/static/chunks/foo.css
# on Railway, which 404s.
#
# The catch-all at the bottom MUST NOT use force=true (or the `!` flag).
# Without force, Netlify serves static files first (homepage, /pricing,
# /plans, /blog, etc.) and only paths that don't match a marketing-site
# file fall through to the proxy.

# Defensive: bare /l (no slug after) shouldn't proxy to Railway with an
# empty splat. Redirect to the homepage so the bad URL doesn't dead-end on
# a 404 page. Specific rule matched before the catch-all.
/l          /                                               301
/l/         /                                               301

# Paths the app itself emits under /l/ (listing pages, /l/{slug}/thanks, agent
# hub thanks) when viewed on this marketing host. Proxy straight through
# WITHOUT re-adding the /l/ prefix — otherwise the catch-all below rewrites
# /l/{x} → /l/l/{x} on Railway → 404. Force (`!`) so it always wins over the
# catch-all. Matched after the bare /l rules above.
/l/*        https://realestate.ctvhomes.com/l/:splat        200!

# Next.js bundles (CSS, JS, fonts, image optimizer). Pass through unchanged.
/_next/*    https://realestate.ctvhomes.com/_next/:splat    200!

# API routes (lead submit, etc). Same — pass through unchanged.
/api/*      https://realestate.ctvhomes.com/api/:splat      200!

# Static assets the Next.js app might reference directly.
/favicon.ico   https://realestate.ctvhomes.com/favicon.ico  200

# Short share URLs for rendered MP4s. ctvhomes.com/v/{adId}?r=v&c=fb resolves
# on the Railway app, which 302s to the actual Supabase render URL. Lets
# agents share a ~38-char link instead of the 140-char Supabase one in
# texts/emails. Force (`!`) so we never try to match these against a
# marketing-page file.
/v/*        https://realestate.ctvhomes.com/v/:splat        200!

# Catch-all for unknown paths only. No `!` so marketing pages keep serving.
/*          https://realestate.ctvhomes.com/l/:splat        200
